:

1. *Misliti* da će sve biti u redu. (Thinking that everything will be okay.)
2. Ona je mislila da će ona biti u pravu. (She thought she would be right.)
3. Ja mislim da je to pogrešno. (I think that's wrong.)
4. Oni su mislili da nema nade. (They thought there was no hope.)
5. Mi mislimo da je ovo najbolje rešenje. (We think this is the best solution.)
6. Njegovo mišljenje je da nema izlaza. (His opinion is that there is no way out.)
7. Oni su se *mislili* da je to dobra ideja. (They thought it was a good idea.)